post_text:
Good afternoon West Lyon families and staff!

The 20-21 school year starts on Monday, August 24th! We also wanted to remind you that school will be dismissed early 1:30 pm as previously scheduled, and we'll dismiss Friday, August 28th at 11:40 am for staff PD.

Also, in looking ahead at next week, temperatures look to be very warm, so please be prepared and plan ahead if we would happen to dismiss early Tuesday through Thursday. Our plan is to alert parents and families as soon as possible of early dismissals if at all possible at least 24 hrs in advance.

Thank you, West Lyon Administration

post_text: West Lyon families, we plan to release our complete Return to Learn Plan as we're waiting for additional guidance from our local and state public health officials, as well as the Iowa Department of Education. The intention of this plan is to provide guidance and information for the families of our district as we return to school on August 24th. We need your understanding that more than likely this plan could change, as we continue to receive additional guidance and information. At West Lyon, we take pride in being able to provide an engaging and safe learning environment, and during these difficult challenges that we face, we need your support! Please click on the CDC link below to read information as it contains information for reopening schools. https://bit.ly/30b1caj

post_text: Iowa's Governor Kim Reynolds just confirmed that Iowa schools will be closed for the remainder of the year. She made this announcement during her morning press conference. West Lyon students and staff will continue with our current learning practices, with additional information to be provided in the coming days. This extension will also keep our building closed for activities through May 31st.

post_text: The West Lyon Community School District will do it's best to update students, staff, parents and community members on the Coronavirus. Please be sure to add: https://idph.iowa.gov/emerging-health-issues/novel-coronavirus and follow these 3 simple procedures to help yourself and other in helping to prevent spread of this virus. 1. Cover your cough 2. Clean your hands 3. Contain the germs (Stay home when your sick). We are also very fortunate that the Lyon County Health Services department communicates with us to better educate us all on preventing the spreading of this virus.
